-Mx6vMqHqwj--cu6MYbn.text: According to a tweet from the Saint Paul Police Department,  Police have arrested a 31-year-old woman in connection to a hostage incident. They have also advised that there were no injuries reported during the incident.

nib.text:
Police detained a woman who held four people hostage at a Speedway gas station in Parkway-Greenbrier Tuesday afternoon, officials said. 

At around 3:10 p.m., police responded to a report of a woman holding a man at gunpoint in the 800 block of Johnson Parkway.

Upon arrival, officers learned a woman had taken four men hostage inside a store. 

Police called negotiators and SWAT to the scene and began working to communicate with the woman. 

At around 4:15 p.m., officers heard a gunshot from inside the store and SWAT entered the building. 

SWAT officers were quickly able to detain the 31-year-old suspect and rescue the four people who were being held, hostage. 

The SPPD later reported the suspect has been booked for threats of violence, second-degree assault and kidnapping.
